From Gregory Dudek Subject Re IIci upgrade In article LOGIN writes A while ago I posted a note asking for specs on the Quadra and opinions on the upgrade of a IIci an accelerator So far no responsed that I've Please let me know what you think of these possible upgrade paths Cost efficiency pros cons Thanks Complete are best obtained from your dealer or some recent copy of MacWorld or My foggy memory suggests that the most relevant comparison factors vis a vis a IIci are as follows MHz Mhz data path don't recall this for sure but it's slower than Q style machines for sure Ethertalk card on board Audio in out MB RAM on motherboard SIMM slots NuBus More flexible build in video than the Uses In comparison a IIci with an accelerator won't give you audio or ethernet or the same video With a accelerator CPU performance can be comparable but I think it ends up costing Greg Dudek